def count_pairs(nums1, nums2, diff):
    n = len(nums1)
    count = 0
    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(i + 1, n):
            if nums1[i] - nums1[j] <= nums2[i] - nums2[j] + diff:
                count += 1
    return count
```

    The algorithm uses a nested loop to iterate through all possible pairs `(i, j)` such that `0 <= i < j <= n - 1`. For each pair, it compares the difference in elements in `nums1` and `nums2` to check if it satisfies the given condition `nums1[i] - nums1[j] <= nums2[i] - nums2[j] + diff`. If the condition is satisfied, increment the count. In the end, return the count which holds the number of pairs that satisfy the conditions.

